{"article_id":"GIGG6QGIswZ2H01x","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Barack Obama says","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"a U.S.-Russian agreement offers a chance","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to destroy Syria 's stockpile of chemical weapons","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"and promises to end the threat","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"they pose to Syrians and the world .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"But the two powers are divided over the fate of Syrian President Bashar Assad .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"Obama ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"speaking in a television interview","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"taped before Saturday 's announcement of the chemical weapons deal ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"said","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Russian President Vladimir Putin is `` protecting '' Assad","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"and does n't share American `` values '' in Syria .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"`` He has a different attitude about the Assad regime , ''","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Obama told ABC 's `` This Week . ''","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"`` But what I 've also said to him directly is that we both have an interest","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"in preventing chaos ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"we both have an interest","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"in preventing terrorism .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"The situation in Syria right now is untenable .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"As long as Mr. Assad 's in power ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"there is going be some sort of conflict there . ''","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Despite Obama 's calls for Assad to leave power ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"Obama reiterated","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"that he would not use military force","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"to achieve that objective .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"securing Syria 's chemical weapons is his `` primary concern . ''","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"In setting out one of the most ambitious arms-control efforts in history ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"the U.S. and Russia reached an agreement","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"to inventory Syria 's chemical weapons program and seize all its components .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"The agreement includes imposing penalties","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"if the Assad government fails to comply .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"In a written statement","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"following the agreement ,","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"Obama said","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"the world expects Syria to live up to its public commitments","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"to hand over its chemical weapons stockpile .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"Warning","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"that the U.S. was prepared to act","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"if Syria falls short ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"he also cautioned","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"that more work remains even after the progress","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"the deal represents .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"The U.S. and others blame Assad 's government for an Aug. 21 gas attack in the suburbs of Damascus , the Syrian capital .","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"Assad denies the charge ,","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"blaming Syrian rebels .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"More than 1,400 people died ,","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"according to U.S. estimates ,","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"the latest victims of Syria 's 2 1/2-year-old civil war .","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"Polls showed relatively little support among Americans for a military strike against Syria ,","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"even after the Obama administration 's efforts","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"to argue","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"that punishing the Assad government","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"for violating international norms of warfare was in the security interests of the U.S .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"Obama ordered preparations for American airstrikes ,","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"but he decided instead to ask for authorization from Congress for military action .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"Then came the Russian proposal for international control of Syria 's chemical weapons ,","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"and Obama asked Congress ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"already largely opposed to military intervention ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"to delay a vote .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"The deal","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"to destroy Syria 's chemical weapons","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"also offers the potential","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"for reviving international peace talks","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"to end a civil war","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"that has claimed more than 100,000 lives","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"and sent 2 million refugees","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"fleeing for safety ,","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"and now threatens the stability of the entire Mideast .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"In Congress , Republican Sens . John McCain of Arizona and Lindsey Graham of South Carolina ,","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"who are among Obama 's sharpest foreign policy critics","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"and support greater U.S. assistance for Syria 's rebels ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"the agreement will embolden enemies such as Iran .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"House Democratic leader Nancy Pelosi of California credited the president 's `` steadfast leadership ''","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"for `` making significant progress in our efforts","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"to prevent the use of weapons of mass destruction . ''","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"© Copyright 2019 The Associated Press .","depth":2},{"id":78,"text":"All rights reserved .","depth":3},{"id":79,"text":"This material may not be published , broadcast , rewritten or redistributed .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":159,"left":156,"right":158,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":122,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"l